(42, 23, 42, 42, 12, 8, 8, 'remember me when thou comest into thy kingdom', 'Confession and Recognition', 'This connection highlights the theme of recognition and confession. In both passages, the act of acknowledging Jesus is central, with the thief asking Jesus to remember him and the call to confess Him before men.', 'theme', 0.37, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
